	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A neat IDE!<br /><br />The only thing that bothers me is this:<br /><br />I like to have my .nes output files go into a subfolder of the source file's folder called /nes/ .<br /><br />I wanted to tell the compiler to output to this subfolder, but none of the radio buttons found in windows-&gt;preferences-&gt;assembler-&gt;NES Compilers that related to the output file really applied.  I changed the compile parameters to:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">${sourceFilePath}&nbsp; ${sourceFolderPath}\nes\${outputFileName}</div><br /><br />But because the IDE only looks for the output in either the source folder, the temp folder, or a fixed folder, there is no way that it can find the output file once it compiles.  It throws a &quot;output file not created&quot; error in the error log, because it is looking in the wrong folder for the output.<br /><br />It would be nice if you could specify an output path that is relative to the source folder, and then I could avoid this problem.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
